<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="645" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2602: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-12T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                                        1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your June 1 [<hi rend="italic">9</hi>], 11 a.m.</p>
                        <p>Department pleased, good man to be Governor of Bluefields but believes
                            fairness demands that Government publicly assume a definite position
                            with respect to expulsion decree. Keep Department informed by cable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>